dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of railways and five classes of roads are shown.  Covers area west from Laage to Bismark to the east, and north from Vorbein to Gransee to the south. Neustrelitz roughly below center left portion of sheet.  Likely reprint of Sheet N.54, Neustrelitz by Army Map Service, U.S. Army from series issued in various editions by Geographical Section, General Staff, No. 4346.  Military grid.  Nord de Guerre Grid ... Spheroid, Du Plessis..  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Cataloging agency's copy printed on verso of unrelated map, Blatt 1, River Tweed, from series with title: England 1:50 000, originally published [Berlin] : [Generalstab des Heeres], [1940]. German series consists of enlargements of the Ordnance Survey Popular Edition one-inch maps published by the German General Staff. Maps distributed by Army Map Service, U.S. Army following capture from foreign military during World War II.  IXA.  Includes legend, Incidence of grid letters diagrams, Convergence for corners of this sheet diagram, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data: Nord de Guerre Grid, Index to adjoining sheets, Index to corresponding sheets of G.S.G.S. 4416, C. Europe 1/100,000 scale sheets, Conversion table, Authorities, and Glossary.
